attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated backdoor and C2 agent. It demonstrates classic malware behavior by daemonizing and replicating itself to '/usr/local/bin/sysd' for stealth. The sample implements extensive persistence across various Linux init systems, including creating a systemd service ('persist.service') explicitly described as the 'NexusCorp C2 Persistence Daemon', appending respawn entries to '/etc/inittab', modifying '/etc/rc.local', and installing an '@reboot' crontab entry. It features network communication capabilities for C2 interaction, uses XOR-based string obfuscation, and contains functionality to execute shell commands via '/bin/sh'.
